717625f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 72nd Street
717625f-a.text:
Broadway (then known as Boulevard), west side, from 72nd to
74th Streets, showing the Hotel St. Andrew in the foreground, and
the Rutgers Memorial Church. The Hotel St. Andrew will stand in
1936, but the church will give way between 1920 and 1925 to a
five-story building.
About 1895.
Brown Brothers.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
According to the New York Times of October 3, 1937, the Hotel built
in 1893, will be replaced by a 4 or 5-story business structure. This
site was the result (to himself and at a total cost of only ~6,500) of
a shrewd land speculation deal, by Robert Robertson in January 1886.
It became the property of Morris Schinasi, the cigarette manufacturer
at a later date si whose heirs are involved in the present transfer.
Nleg 4t2Al
